{{IPA|/ɗ/}} is a [[voiced retroflex plosive]]. It may have an [[implosive]] quality for some speakers.

The voiceless stops {{IPA|/t/}} and {{IPA|/k/}} are always aspirated.

{{IPA|/d/}} and {{IPA|/t/}} are [[dental consonants|dental]]

The velar fricative {{IPA|[x]}} is mainly used in the eastern dialect (Harar) as a phoneme. It is represented as {{angbr|kh}} in the [[Oromo orthography|Oromo script]] (''Qubee'') though it is pronounced as a {{angbr|k}} in most other dialects.{{sfnp|Lloret|1997|p=495}}

==Vowels==
Oromo has five vowels which all contrast long and short vowels. Sometimes there is a change in vowel quality when the vowel is short. Short vowels tend to be more centralized than their counterparts.

Though sometimes diphthongs may occur, there are none that occur in a word's unaltered form.

